Steals are part of the stolen team's shot clock and possession.

# END OF POSSESSION SIGNALERS
Steals.
Possession is DEFENSE and a rebound is grabbed.
Possession is OFFENSE and misses a shot and next entry possession is DEFENSE (also indicates an opposing team rebound).
Possession is OFFENSE and my player commits a foul.
A shot is made and possession flips on next entry.
Made or missed free throw is followed by possession change.


# Opposing team rebound.
Possession is OFFENSE and misses a shot and next entry possession is DEFENSE 
Possession is DEFENSE when a shot is missed and next entry is not DEFENSE with REBOUND or TEAM_REBOUND.